The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                The state government on Tuesday forwarded to La Martiniere for Boys the recommendation of the National Commission for Protection of Child Rights for appropriate action against the principal and four other teachers accused of inflicting physical and mental torture on Rouvanjit Rawla, a Class VIII student of the school who committed suicide on February 12. The commission has recommended that the principal be removed and the salary increment of the four other teachers be withheld.    A fire broke out on the second floor of Central Bank of India on NS Road on Tuesday afternoon following a short-circuit. Four tenders doused the fire in 30 minutes. Some monitors and a few files and documents were destroyed.    A bill to acquire Acharya Bhavan, the house of Sir Jagadish Chandra Bose at 93 APC Roy Road, and turn it into a museum was passed in the Assembly on Tuesday.   he house, built by Bose in 1902, has his personal belongings, scientific instruments, art collection and other memorabilia.    An 45-year-old man was seriously injured after being hit by a speeding bus on route 234 in front of St James School on AJC Bose Road on Tuesday. Residents took him to NRS Medical College and Hospital where he succumbed to his injuries.                                                                                                                                               
